  <section id="pathways">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400 mb-4">§3 — Neural Pathways: How the Brain is Wired</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6">

      <!-- Sensory pathways -->
      <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-kernel-700 rounded-lg p-5">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-3">Sensory Input Pathways</h3>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-4 border border-kernel-800">
            <h4 class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-400 mb-2">Visual Pathway</h4>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[10px] text-kernel-400 flex-wrap">
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded">Retina</span>
              <span class="text-kernel-600">→</span>
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded text-rose-400">LGN</span>
              <span class="text-kernel-600">→</span>
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded text-blue-400">V1 (Occipital)</span>
              <span class="text-kernel-600">→</span>
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded text-blue-400">V2/V4</span>
              <span class="text-kernel-600">→</span>
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded text-blue-400">Temporal (what)</span>
              <span class="text-kernel-600">/</span>
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded text-blue-400">Parietal (where)</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-[10px] text-kernel-500 mt-2">
              The lateral geniculate nucleus (LGN) is the thalamic relay for vision.
              Its resolution_dependence = 0.90 — one of the highest in the atlas,
              because its 6 layers are only resolvable at ultra-high resolution.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-4 border border-kernel-800">
            <h4 class="text-xs font-bold text-green-400 mb-2">Auditory Pathway</h4>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[10px] text-kernel-400 flex-wrap">
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded">Cochlea</span>
              <span class="text-kernel-600">→</span>
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded text-amber-400">Brainstem nuclei</span>
              <span class="text-kernel-600">→</span>
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded text-rose-400">MGN</span>
              <span class="text-kernel-600">→</span>
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded text-blue-400">A1 (Temporal)</span>
              <span class="text-kernel-600">→</span>
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded text-blue-400">Wernicke's area</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-[10px] text-kernel-500 mt-2">
              The medial geniculate nucleus (MGN) relays auditory information to cortex.
              Like LGN, it has very high resolution_dependence (0.90) and very low
              volumetric_fraction (0.03) — classic geometric slaughter pattern.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-kernel-950 rounded p-4 border border-kernel-800">
            <h4 class="text-xs font-bold text-purple-400 mb-2">Motor Pathway</h4>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[10px] text-kernel-400 flex-wrap">
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded text-blue-400">Prefrontal (plan)</span>
              <span class="text-kernel-600">→</span>
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded text-blue-400">Motor cortex</span>
              <span class="text-kernel-600">→</span>
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded text-pink-400">Corticospinal tract</span>
              <span class="text-kernel-600">→</span>
              <span class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-kernel-800 rounded">Spinal cord</span>
